Ingredients:
 - 1/4 container (about 3 3/4 cups) full-fat plain yogurt
 - 1 cup sugar
 - 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt

Directions:
  1. Whisk yogurt, sugar, and salt together in a mixing bowl until sugar has
  completely dissolved. Chill in an ice bath or refrigerate until yogurt
  registers at least 45Â°F on an instant-read thermometer.
  2. Churn yogurt in ice cream machine according to manufacturer's instructions.
   Transfer ice cream to airtight container and chill in freezer for at least 4
   to 5 hours before serving.
